HB 396 Original 2026 Regular Session McMakin
Abstract: Provides relative to the admissibility of autopsy photographs in first or second
degree murder trials.
Proposed law provides that a photograph of an autopsy conducted by a coroner is admissible
in any criminal proceeding that alleges a violation of first degree murder (R.S. 14:30) or
second degree murder (R.S. 14:30.1).
(Adds C.E. Art. 416)
